sts": "", "*": "Pengolodh"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Penlod"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Place of the Well"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Qenya"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Quenta Silmarillion"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Road of Arches"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Road of Pomps"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Rog"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Salgant"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Seven Gates of Gondolin"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Square of the Palace"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Sting"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "The Book of Lost Tales"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "The Book of Lost Tales Part Two"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "The Fall of Gondolin"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "The Fall of Gondolin (chapter)"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "The Lay of the Fall of Gondolin"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "The Silmarillion"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "The Wanderings of Húrin"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "The War of the Jewels"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Tower of the King"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Tumladen"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Tuor"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Turgon"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Twelve houses of the Gondothlim"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Ulmo"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Ulmo's warning"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Unfinished Tales"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Voronwë"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Wanderings of Húrin"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Warden of the Great Gate"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Way of Running Waters"}, {"ns": 0, "*": "Iron Guards"}, {"ns": 14, "exists": "", "*": "Category:Images by Alarie"}], "templates": [{"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:Rp"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:References"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:UT"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:S"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:WJ"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:Webcite"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:LT2"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:Gondolin"}], "images": ["Alarie_-_The_First_Gate.jpg"], "wikitext": {"*": "[[File:Alarie - The First Gate.jpg|thumb|right|250px|''The First Gate'' by [[:Category:Images by Alarie|Alarie]]]]\nThe '''Orfalch Echor''' was the great ravine through the [[Dry River]] of the [[Encircling Mountains]] by which [[Gondolin]] was approached.\n\n== History ==\nThe Orfalch Echor was the route that [[Elemmakil]] led [[Tuor]] and [[Voronwë]] through to meet [[Ecthelion|Ecthelion of the Fountain]]. At its lower end was the First Gate, the [[Gate of Wood]]. The Orfalch continued through the remainder of the [[Seven Gates of Gondolin]], reaching the Seventh Gate, the [[Gate of Steel]]. At the upper end was a high sward that offered a view of [[Tumladen]] and the city in its center.<ref>{{UT|Tuor}}</ref><ref>{{S|23}}</ref>\n\nDuring [[Húrin|Húrin's]] [[The Wanderings of Húrin|wanderings]], he came upon the Orfalch Echor, only to find the old Way of Escape buried underneath ''\"a great fall of stones beneath a sheer rock-wall\"''.<ref>{{WJ|Hurin}}, pp. 271, 302</ref>\n\n== Etymology ==\nThe name ''Orfalch Echor'' is suggested by Paul Strack to be a combination of [[Noldorin]] ''or'' (\"above\"), ''falch'' (\"cleft\"), and ''echor'' (\"outer circle\"), perhaps meaning \"High Cleft of the Outer Circle\".<ref>{{webcite|author=Paul Strack|articleurl=http://eldamo.org/content/words/word-677947469.html|articlename=S. ''Orfalch Echor'' loc.|website=Eldamo|accessed=16 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Other versions of the legendarium ==\nIn ''[[The Fall of Gondolin (chapter)|The Book of Lost Tales]]'', the '''Way of Escape''' was the main entrance to [[Gondolin]], and it was not a natural ravine, but was instead built by the [[Gondothlim]] to be used by those [[Noldoli]] who escaped from [[Melko]]<ref name=LT>{{LT2|III}}</ref>{{rp|163}} and as a way of escape in case the city was attacked, as it eventually was. Because of [[Maeglin|Meglin's]] treason, Melko was aware of this pass, so many survivors were killed there by a monster while trying to escape quickly in spite of [[Idril|Idril's]] warnings.<ref name=LT />{{rp|189}}\n\nThis way is also known as ''Bad Uthwen'' in [[Gnomish]] and ''Uswevandë'' in [[Qenya]].<ref name=LT />{{rp|336}}\n\n{{References}}\n\n{{gondolin}}\n\n[[Category:Cliffs and ravines]]\n[[Category:Gondolin]]\n[[Category:Passes]]\n[[Category:Sindarin locations]]\n\n[[fr:encyclo/geographie/routes/orfalch echor]]"}}}